output.crosstab_text:
For first degree graduates of Allied health, 1 years after graduation, Construction was the most common industry for and White ethnicity graduates, Wholesale and retail trade - repair of motor vehicles and motorcycles was the most common industry for and Black ethnicity graduates, Other service activities was the most common industry for and Asian ethnicity graduates, Administrative and support service activities was the most common industry for and Mixed ethnicity graduates, Human health and social work activities was the most common industry for and Other ethnicity graduates, and Public administration and defence - compulsory social security was the most common industry for and Not known ethnicity graduates.

The industry with the largest range in proportions was Administrative and support service activities where Mixed ethnicity graduates had the highest proportion and Black ethnicity graduates had the lowest proportion.The industry with the largest range in median earnings was Arts, entertainment and recreation where Mixed ethnicity graduates the highest median earnings (£27,100) and White ethnicity graduates had the lowest median earnings (£22,700).The group with the highest median earnings was Mixed ethnicity graduates in the Other service activities industry (median earnings of £27,900).
